<div class="prose prose-lg">

<h2 id="customer-support">Customer Support Quality</h2>

<p>Service Fusion provides phone support 6am-6pm PST with typical wait times under 5 minutes. Email responses average 2-4 hours during business days. The platform includes unlimited training sessions and dedicated account managers for teams over 10 users.</p>

<p>Jobber offers 24/7 chat support plus phone support during business hours. Response times average under 2 minutes for chat, 3-7 minutes for phone calls. However, Jobber doesn't provide dedicated account management or custom training sessions.</p>

<p>Based on contractor feedback, Service Fusion's support team understands HVAC workflows better. Representatives can troubleshoot complex scheduling scenarios and provide industry-specific configuration advice. Jobber's support is faster but more generic.</p>

<p>Implementation support differs dramatically. Service Fusion assigns a dedicated implementation specialist for 30-60 days, includes data migration assistance, and provides custom workflow setup. Jobber offers self-service setup with optional paid consultation ($150/hour).</p>

</div>

<div class="prose prose-lg">

<h2 id="which-is-better">Which Platform Wins for HVAC Companies?</h2>

<p>Choose Service Fusion if you have:</p>
<ul>
<li>8+ team members (cost savings become significant)</li>
<li>Complex HVAC operations (commercial, multi-day projects)</li>
<li>Heavy inventory management needs</li>
<li>Advanced reporting requirements</li>
<li>Multiple permission levels needed</li>
</ul>

<p>Choose Jobber if you have:</p>
<ul>
<li>3-7 team members (lower entry cost)</li>
<li>Primarily residential service calls</li>
<li>High technician turnover (easier training)</li>
<li>Simple workflow requirements</li>
<li>Priority on mobile app performance</li>
</ul>

<p>The break-even point occurs around 7 users. Below this threshold, Jobber costs less and provides adequate functionality for most HVAC operations. Above 7 users, Service Fusion delivers better value through cost savings and advanced features.</p>

<p>Migration complexity favors staying with your current platform unless the cost difference exceeds $2,000 annually. Both platforms require 2-4 weeks for complete data migration and team training.</p>

<div style="background-color: #e8f4fd; border-left: 4px solid #2563eb; padding: 16px; margin: 24px 0;">
<p><strong>Growth Consideration:</strong> If you plan to hire 3+ people in the next 18 months, choose Service Fusion now to avoid migration costs later.</p>
</div>

<p>For contractors comparing multiple platforms, consider reading our detailed guides on <a href="/hvac/crm/jobber-vs-servicetitan">Jobber vs ServiceTitan</a> and <a href="/hvac/crm/best-crm-for-small-hvac-companies">the best CRM options for small HVAC companies</a>.</p>

</div>

